    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cleaning method that removes soil, discolorations, or coatings through the action of certain materials which impact and abrade the surface under pressure.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000017491/Grimmer,  Historic Masonry Deterioration Problems (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Método de limpieza que elimina la suciedad, decoloraciones o revestimientos a través de la acción de determinados materiales a presión que impactan y desgastan la superficie.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
